Rating: 3
I used homemade greek-style yogurt from 2% milk, thinned with a little leftover whey and milk instead of water. Instead of the one loaf, I made several mini-loafs and cupcakes, and you should definitely not fill anything more than a 1/2 to 2/3 full. This batter gets really fluffy as it bakes. I'm going to try freezing some of the mini loaves and see how they hold up...

Rating: 2
Followed one cook's advice and replaced water with yogurt. All other instructions followed to a "T" save for using a larger loaf pan (9x5"). Maybe my oven is off, but this took 20 minutes more to bake and it oozed out of the pan and wound up on the pizza stone at the bottom of my oven. Water would have made the batter even more liquidy so I can't blame the yogurt. Great chocolate flavor, very moist on inside. Think I'll try as muffins next time around.

Rating: 4
I have made this cake many times since this recipe was first published and expect to make it many times in the futere. Each time it turns out perfectly. The recipe tin size is a misprint I think. The loaf pan that I used holds 7 cups (I measured it) you will need one at least 6 cups in volume.

