Rating: 3
Did I make "the" recipe or not? You decide. Used 1-1/3c buttermilk (out of yogurt), 8T butter (to compensate for low fat in buttermilk vs yogurt), 3/4c sugar (to make more chocolatey), added 2t Penzeys cake spice, a great blend. The result was a simple cake, like a moist (and lower calorie) chocolate pound cake, good enough in its simplicity. Would be great w strawberries, whipped cream.

Rating: 3
I thought this was a great cake. I used a 175g (6 oz) container of full fat Astro yogurt that made for a very moist cake. I used Ghirardelli cocoa, and the cake turned out rich an chocolately. It definitely tasted sinful, which I didn't expect. I baked it in three mini loaf pans, with no overflow, for about 45 mins.

