Rating: 3
I made this cake the day before yesterday for a friend's birthday. One thing puzzled me and that was the size of the pan (8 1/2 by 4 1/2 by 2/12). I have an 8 1/2 inch loaf pan which is 4 1/2 inches high and 4 1/2 inches wide, which I used, but was aghast when I realized that the batter filled the entire pan almost to the rim. It still turned out great (I received a lot of compliments) but while it was baking I was constantly afraid the batter would flow over the edge of the pan. I have yet to find a loaf pan with higher sides. Would it make sense to divide the batter in half and use two loaf pans? P.S. I made a Philadelphia Cream Cheese frosting which was really yummy - everyone loved it)

